{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"52433b7b-76e6-41d8-bfa1-f3cbc2a40686","content":"### 3. GitHub Environment\n\nCreate a **`nuget`** environment in your repo settings:\n**Settings → Environments → New environment → name it `nuget`**\n\n(Optionally add protection rules like required reviewers.)\n\n---\n\n### How it works\n\n- No API key needed. The `id-token: write` permission lets the runner request an OIDC token.\n- NuGet.org validates the token against your trusted publisher registration (org, repo, workflow, environment).\n- `dotnet nuget push` without `--api-key` works because NuGet.org accepts the OIDC token from the environment.\n\n### To publish\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0 && git push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe workflow triggers on version tags. Make sure your `.csproj` sets `<PackageId>` and `<Version>` appropriately.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"16858f28-a11e-4ad6-b87e-b1d74b08e588","outputTokens":205,"requestId":"B80B:26A05B:D15084:EFA4B7:69F2A84B"},"id":"b61b934c-356c-41f5-baaa-29de4bc95834","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:54:41.879Z","parentId":"ac80bf02-2e22-4f30-8d52-73430c1684cb"}
